template.name: Template APP asuswrt xDSL
template.description:
Monitor some DSL line properties that the normal Linux template does not monitor. Tested with a Asus DSL-AC68U, may work on others.
Mainly parses contents from /tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt
/tmp/adsl/ needs to be readable by the user running zabbix. (using zabbix-agent from entware)
One UserParameter can be added to the configuration to check the firmware version as set in the nvram. UserParameter=nvram.get_version,echo "$(nvram get firmver).$(nvram get buildno)_$(nvram get extendno)"

item.name: xDSL Link Uptime
item.description:
Save some values in case more work needs to be done on preprocessing for the link up seconds item in this template need to check what happens for 2+ Weeks, 1+ Month, 1+ Year...
ADSLUpTime= 3:14, 21 secs
Some examples to test with:
9 days, 9:54, 19 secs 3 min, 0 secs 23:59, 41 secs 1 day, 1 min, 41 secs 59 min, 47 secs 1:01, 47 secs 1 day, 9:56, 41 secs 1 day, 10:04, 41 secs 6:04, 41 secs 6:02, 41 secs 10 days, 2 min, 9 secs 10 days, 0 min, 9 secs 9 days, 23:56, 9 secs 9 days, 23:54, 19 secs 9 days, 23:52, 9 secs 1:02, 41 secs 1:00, 41 secs 58 min, 41 secs 56 min, 41 secs

item.name: xDSL Link Uptime seconds
item.description: May break or be undefined in some cases.

item.name: xDSL Link Uptime seconds DEBUG
item.description: Save the Regex output for testing the link up seconds item

item.name: Router Firmware Version
item.description: UserParameter=nvram.get_version,echo "$(nvram get firmver).$(nvram get buildno)_$(nvram get extendno)"

item.name: DSL Driver Version
item.description:
In the modem web GUI, this is called: DSL Driver Version
DSL firmware + hardware version on same line.
Available in: /tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt and /tmp/adsl/adsl_fwver
Since info_adsl.txt might not always be visible ( between updates) use adsl_fwver

item.name: DSL Firmware Version
item.description: In the modem web GUI, this is called: DSL Firmware Version Found in the file: /tmp/adsl/fwver.conf

item.name: info_adsl.txt contents
item.description:
vfs.file.contents[/tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt]
master item for dependent items to parse

trigger.name: Change in DSLAM vendor id
trigger.description: Value for FarEndVendorID in /tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt has changed

trigger.name: Does "/tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt" exist
trigger.description: The file "/tmp/adsl/info_adsl.txt" either does not exist or is not readable by the zabbix agent

trigger.name: DSL Driver Version has changed
trigger.description: The DSL Driver version has changed. Probably due to a Firmware update.

trigger.expression: {Template APP asuswrt xDSL:dsl.info.lineState.iregexp(up)}=0 and {Template APP asuswrt xDSL:dsl.info.lineState.prev()}=0
trigger.name: DSL linestate not up
trigger.description: Sometimes this happens because the adsl.txt file was not there when checking for the state. So check for this to be true two consecutive checks before triggering.

trigger.expression: {Template APP asuswrt xDSL:dsl.info.lineState.iregexp(up)}<>1 and {Template APP asuswrt xDSL:dsl.info.lineState.iregexp(up,#2)}<>1
trigger.name: DSL linestate not up2
trigger.description: Might be this doesn't need to be checked from last two now that it is a dependant item.

trigger.name: DSL link has been restarted
trigger.description:
Basically DSL link is uptime is less than previously measured.
Probably indicating one of the following - indicating a restart of the modem - disconnection ( and reconnection of the link?) - a clock counter rollover (unlikely) - unanticipated error in converting the info in /tmp/adsl/asdl_info.txt to seconds

trigger.name: DSL link up for less than one hour
trigger.description: DSL link uptime less than one hour
